OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F386A1769526716
OL,3,CLack of whistleblowing legislation
OL,4,Cleaving islanders in Guernsey
OL,5,Cvulnerable
OL,7,F"It is understandable that
OL,8,Fwhistleblowers are sometimes worried
OL,9,Fabout possible repercussions", it
OL,10,Fcontinues, "(but) The States of
OL,11,FGuernsey will support and protect from
OL,12,Fvictimisation anyone who raises
OL,13,Fgenuine concerns, in good faith, under
OL,14,Fthis policy, even if they turn out to
OL,15,Fbe mistaken."
OL,17,FBut Sally argues without formal
OL,18,Flegislation in place to reinforce
OL,19,Femployers' duties, this policy "is not
OL,20,Fworth the paper its written on."
OL,26,@rD@MpmrD@Qpn
